server creating
==================
nodejs+express

basic command--->
==================
1)npm init -for creating package.json
2)npm i express-for installing express and creation of node modules
3)instal mongoose - npm i  mongoose

basic steps
===================
1)create a folder for server,
2)create package.json
3)create nodemodules or install express
4)create index.js
5)impost express in index.js file
6)create an application using express
6)set port number
7)resolve http requests
        get-get the data
        post -post the data
        put-update data partially
        patch-update data completely
        delete-delete the data completely

10)jwt token
===================
        install jwt token - npm i jsonwebtoken
        to generate a token - sign()


11)status code
===================
1xx - information
2xx - successful
3xx - redirection
4xx - client erroe
5xx - server error

12)Middleware
=======================
It comes in the middle of the request and response cycle of nodejs execution process.
        i)  application specific middleware - req,res, next - middleware for entire application
        ii) router specific middleware - middleware for specific router - to validate token - we use  verify() in jsonwebtoken

12)database integration
================================
        i)instal mongoose - npm i mongoose connection btw mongodb and server
        ii)import mongose
        iii)connection link
        iiii)creatin db model


13>asynchronous function resolving - promise
=====================================================
        i)resolve state - .then()
        ii)reject state - catch()
        

14)cors-cross  origin resource sharing 
=========================================
===>communication btw frontend and server
        - intall  => npm i cors

        port 4200(angular)----request--->port 3000(node)req received

14)backend
=========
 asynchronous call -RxJs - Reactive extension for javascript
        1) observable
        1a)resolved - subscribe()
        1b)reject - catch()
        

js-promise
ts-RxJs(library)

